{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-01304/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-01304"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:13:04"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, pan"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A waitress glimpses behind her at a man offscreen."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01304/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-01304","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01304/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-01304"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01304/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01304/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01304/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01304/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01304/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01304/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01304/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01304/canvas/1/f5320412-3f79-4235-9bab-037b4343c905","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T20:06:51.506Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Preparation for filming involved no rehearsals and only a short meeting between Daniel Day-Lewis and Vicky Krieps (American Film Institute, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW10047570 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2YicmOOxOg8\"><u>Paul Thomas Anderson</u></a>”). Furthermore, Daniel Day-Lewis encouraged Vicky Krieps to avoid contact with him or Lesley Manville until shooting began, desiring a more authentic initial connection to be captured in the process. Alma crashing into a table wasn’t in the script, so the smile Alma flashes Reynolds and her blushing are Krieps’s genuine response (Ugwu, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW10047570 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2017/12/26/movies/daniel-day-lewis-and-paul-thomas-anderson-on-how-they-created-phantom-thread.html?action=click&amp;module=RelatedCoverage&amp;pgtype=Article&amp;region=Footer\"><u>Daniel Day-Lewis and Paul Thomas Anderson</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01304/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:552.5364963503648,77.86861313868616,636.4160583941606,973.6313868613139"}}}]}]}]}